\i \cf0 Directions
\i0 \
This pork sauce is easy to make and works well with pork and turkey. For making this pomegranate sauce for turkey or pork take a medium saucepan. Add the cranberries to the sugar and pomegranate juice and bring the mixture to a simmer. Cook the sauce over moderate heat, stirring occasionally for around ten minutes. This allows the cranberries to become soft and open up. Now scrape out the thickened pomegranate cranberry juice into a medium bowl and let it stand until cool, about 2 hours. While serving add the pomegranate seeds and serve the sauce chilled. The best thing about this sauce is that it can be made beforehand and refrigerated for about two weeks.\
